1. Create Notebook (V1/V2 API) Initiates a new notebook execution request,
allocating required resources and returning the run id.
2. Get Notebook (V1/V2 API) - Retrieves the current execution status and
metadata of a specific notebook run, including progress, output, and runtime details.
3. Cancel Notebook (V1/V2 API) - Sends a termination command to stop an
active notebook execution and release associated compute resources.
4. Retriger Notebook (V1/V2 API) - Re-executes a previously completed or
failed notebook run using the same configuration, enabling retry or regeneration scenarios.
